-- Unitech’s Third-Quarter Profit Drops 50% as Home Sales Decline
-- B y   P o o j a   T h a k u r
-- 2012-02-14T15:24:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-14/unitech-s-third-quarter-profit-drops-50-as-home-sales-decline.html
Unitech Ltd. (UT) , India’s third-largest
developer by value, said third-quarter profit slid 50 percent on
lower home sales.  Profit in the three months ended Dec. 31 dropped to 552
million rupees ($11 million), lower than the 1.02 billion rupee
median of 16 estimates  compiled  by Bloomberg. Sales slid 23
percent to 5.1 billion rupees, according to a statement from the
company.  Sales in the National Capital Region, which includes  New
Delhi  and its surrounding areas, gained 27 percent to 22.77
million square feet in the quarter ended December, according to
Liases Foras Real Estate Rating & Research Pvt. The weighted
average selling price climbed to 3,394.72 rupees a square foot,
5 percent higher than the September quarter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pooja Thakur in Singapore at 
